  "body": "#### System information\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : current master - f83fc302a504\r\n\r\n\r\nI have some generated bindings and calling `func (c *BoundContract) Transact` returns an error \r\n```\r\n<error(*github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/rpc.jsonError)>)\r\nCode: -32000\r\nMessage: \"nonce too low\"\r\nData: nil\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow the caller needs to match this against the `core.ErrNonceTooLow` , but since it is wrapped in `jsonError` this is not possible.\r\n\r\nThe end goal is to be able to use something like\r\n```\r\nif err == core.ErrNonceTooLow\r\n\tNonce = Nonce + 1\r\nor\r\nif errors.Is(err, core.ErrNonceTooLow) {\r\n\tNonce = Nonce + 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think the solution would be to expose `Is` method to `jsonError` and this will work nicely. ",
