    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Unfortunately it is not as easy as exposing the `Is` method on `jsonError` since the `jsonError` object does not have the error information. It only contains the error message not the actual error object. Since the `jsonError` has to be send over the wire it has to be marshaled into json. This will afaik result in loosing the error field if we were to put a raw `Error error` field into the `jsonError`. \r\nCurrently the only working solution is to check the error string, which I agree is super brittle and shouldn't be done.\r\nIn theory we should use the error code to convey this information, but these are not standardized yet.\r\nI'll convert this bug report into a feature request if that's cool with you?",
